            {
              "id": "shared2017m_s2_text_prompt_1",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Read the text carefully and do the activities."
            },
            {
              "id": "shared2017m_s2_text_prompt_2",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Bullying is when someone keeps saying or doing things to have power over you. This includes calling you stupid names, saying nasty things about you, leaving you out of activities, not talking to you, threatening, making you feel uncomfortable or scared, taking or damaging your things, hitting or kicking you, or even making you do things you don’t want to do. Moreover, you can also be bullied by someone’s lack of attention or reaction."
            },
            {
              "id": "shared2017m_s2_text_prompt_3",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "It is estimated that about 20% of all students are bullied in school at any time, and about half have experienced bullying at some points before. Bullied students can feel unhappy, afraid, uncomfortable, depressed, hurt and alone. Therefore, many of them begin to perform poorly in academic work. Some end up dropping out of school. They may suffer depression and anxiety. They suffer eating and sleep disorders and lose interest in activities they used to enjoy."
            },
            {
              "id": "shared2017m_s2_text_prompt_4",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Adapted from: http://eschooltoday.com"
            },
            {
              "id": "shared2017m_s2_text_prompt_5",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Nii Noi Odonkor"
            }
          ]
        },
